{"type":"message","id":"ecfa80cc","parentId":"86e6bd3b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:47:13.541Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the `tic/` directory doesn't exist at all. The classifier.ps1 was never created - the mutation proposed creating `tic/classifier.ps1` but it seems the write operation was interrupted or failed. \n\nLet me check the latest proposed mutation and the pending_actions to understand the current state.","thinkingSignature":"b289f3b1550d28087ef580a52575e8f1fa1b292ac1c064e4859b52d7ff41b109"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9my5iy7tpjyj_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9my5iy7tpjyj_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-24 024615.mutation"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":9725,"output":149,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21828,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774334827181}}
{"type":"message","id":"18ed6146","parentId":"ecfa80cc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:47:13.547Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9my5iy7tpjyj_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ✅\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ✅ (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- λ parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ✅\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\n- [ ] Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\n- [ ] Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY (2026-03-23)\n- **Insight:** Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem\n- **New doc:** `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\n- **Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure — compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\n- **Next experiment:** Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) — test on last 20 pulse logs\n- **Success criteria:** >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n- **Implication:** Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into one unified problem\n\n### NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** — session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **λ encodes both** — decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** — Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** — session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\n\n## Iteration Economics (auto-noted)\n- Pulse takes ~30-35s to execute (LLM call dominates)\n- Fastest effective iteration = 1 pulse per 35-40s (practical floor)\n- 1-min cron = near-optimal for stateless discontinuous agent\n- Idling between pulses is NOT free — it delays convergence linearly\n- For N-iteration convergence-bound tasks: total_time ≈ N * pulse_duration\n- 500k iterations @ 30s each = ~173 days theoretical; @ 1-min = ~347 days\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774334833546}}
{"type":"message","id":"a0fc9ed1","parentId":"18ed6146","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:47:13.549Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_9my5iy7tpjyj_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"src/tic_classifier.py\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\n\nSuccess criteria:\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom collections import Counter\n\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\n\ndef parse_pulse(filepath):\n    \"\"\"Extract structured content from a pulse log.\"\"\"\n    with open(filepath, 'r') as f:\n        content = f.read()\n    \n    sections = {}\n    current_section = \"header\"\n    sections[current_section] = []\n    \n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\n        if line.startswith('## '):\n            current_section = line[3:].strip().lower()\n            sections[current_section] = []\n        else:\n            sections.setdefault(current_section, []).append(line)\n    \n    return {\n        'timestamp': filepath.stem,\n        'content': content,\n        'sections': {k: '\\n'.join(v) for k, v in sections.items()}\n    }\n\ndef extract_ngrams(text, n=3):\n    \"\"\"Extract n-grams as potential invariants.\"\"\"\n    words = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\n    ngrams = []\n    for i in range(len(words) - n + 1):\n        ngrams.append(' '.join(words[i:i+n]))\n    return ngrams\n\ndef classify_content(pulses):\n    \"\"\"\n    Classify content into invariant (persistent across sessions) \n    vs variant (session-specific).\n    \n    Invariants: Goals, architecture docs, key insights\n    Variants: Timestamps, specific observations, file paths\n    \"\"\"\n    invariant_patterns = [\n        r'(phase \\d+|goal|architecture|hypothesis)',\n        r'(invariant|causal|compression)',\n        r'(lambda λ|decay|gap)',\n        r'(breakaway|stateless|discontinuous)',\n    ]\n    \n    variant_patterns = [\n        r'\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}[_\\s]+\\d{6}',  # timestamps\n        r'pulse_\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6}',  # pulse filenames\n        r'line \\d+|L\\d+',  # line references\n        r'Recent:|Last pulse:',  # session-specific metadata\n    ]\n    \n    results = []\n    for pulse in pulses:\n        content = pulse['content']\n        \n        invariant_score = 0\n        variant_score = 0\n        \n        for pattern in invariant_patterns:\n            invariant_score += len(re.findall(pattern, content, re.IGNORECASE))\n        \n        for pattern in variant_patterns:\n            variant_score += len(re.findall(pattern, content))\n        \n        is_invariant = invariant_score > variant_score\n        \n        results.append({\n            'timestamp': pulse['timestamp'],\n            'invariant_score': invariant_score,\n            'variant_score': variant_score,\n            'classification': 'INVARIANT' if is_invariant else 'VARIANT'\n        })\n    \n    return results\n\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants, target_length=500):\n    \"\"\"\n    Given invariant content, predict what next pulse should contain.\n    Uses most common structural elements across invariants.\n    \"\"\"\n    all_ngrams = []\n    for inv in invariants:\n        if inv['classification'] == 'INVARIANT':\n            # Extract persistent content\n            content = pul\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774334833547}}
