{"type":"message","id":"4596c4f4","parentId":"6b3c6c14","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:47:40.940Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me check the most recent pulse (024615) to see what actually happened in this cycle.","thinkingSignature":"80c2f5e42cb15b3552364e6f5cfc251caef23e55a28407311e5592372369c6af"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1ij9h8pl9moa_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 024615.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12746,"output":74,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24774,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774334858140}}
{"type":"message","id":"11b17364","parentId":"4596c4f4","timestamp":"2026-03-24T06:47:40.944Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1ij9h8pl9moa_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 024615\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: tic/classifier.ps1 (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action I can take to advance the TIC Experiment goal.\r\n\r\nThe next action is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files. This is the immediate next step for Phase 1 advancement.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist and what I need to create. I should:\r\n1. Implement a TIC classifier\r\n2. The classifier needs to analyze pulse logs to find invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Then predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script for the TIC classifier. I'll need to:\r\n1. Read the pulse log files\r\n2. Implement a simple invariant/variant classifier\r\n3. Test on recent pulse logs\r\n4. Measure classification accuracy\r\n\r\nFirst, let me check what pulse log files exist.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next concrete step for Phase 1. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs to test the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a Python TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs to classify invariant/variant content and tests next-pulse prediction from invariants.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nPULSE_PATTERN = re.compile(r\"pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md\")\r\n\r\ndef parse_pulse(filepath):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structured content from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(filepath, 'r') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    \r\n    sections = {}\r\n    current_section = \"header\"\r\n    sections[current_section] = []\r\n    \r\n    for line in content.split('\\n'):\r\n        if line.startswith('## '):\r\n            current_section = line[3:].strip().lower()\r\n            sections[current_section] = []\r\n        else:\r\n            sections.setdefault(current_section, []).append(line)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'timestamp': filepath.stem,\r\n        'content': content,\r\n        'sections': {k: '\\n'.join(v) for k, v in sections.items()}\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef extract_ngrams(text, n=3):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract n-grams as potential invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    words = re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n    ngrams = []\r\n    for i in range(len(words) - n + 1):\r\n        ngrams.append(' '.join(words[i:i+n]))\r\n    return ngrams\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classify content into invariant (persistent across sessions) \r\n    vs variant (session-specific).\r\n    \r\n    Invariants: Goals, architecture docs, key insights\r\n    Variants: Timestamps, specific observations, file paths\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    invariant_patterns = [\r\n        r'(phase \\d+|goal|architecture|hypothesis)',\r\n        r'(invariant|causal|compression)',\r\n        r'(lambda λ|decay|gap)',\r\n        r'(breakaway|stateless|discontinuous)',\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    variant_patterns = [\r\n        r'\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}[_\\s]+\\d{6}',  # timestamps\r\n        r'pulse_\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6}',  # pulse filenames\r\n        r'line \\d+|L\\d+',  # line references\r\n        r'Recent:|Last pulse:',  # session-specific metadata\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    results = []\r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        content = pulse['content']\r\n        \r\n        invariant_score = 0\r\n        variant_score = 0\r\n        \r\n        for pattern in invariant_patterns:\r\n            invariant_score += len(re.findall(pattern, content, re.IGNORECASE))\r\n        \r\n        for pattern in variant_patterns:\r\n            variant_score += len(re.findall(pattern, content))\r\n        \r\n        is_invariant = invariant_score > variant_score\r\n        \r\n        results.append({\r\n            'timestamp': pulse['timestamp'],\r\n            'invariant_score': invariant_score,\r\n            'variant_score': variant_score,\r\n            'classification': 'INVARIANT' if is_invariant else 'VARIANT'\r\n        })\r\n    \r\n    return results\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants, target_length=500):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Given invariant content, predict what next pulse should contain.\r\n    Uses most common structural elements across invariants.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    all_ngrams = []\r\n    for inv in invariants:\r\n        if inv['classification'] == 'INVARIANT':\r\n            # Extract persistent content\r\n            content = pul\r\nfile: src/tic_classifier.py\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 02:46:43\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774334860943}}
