ral Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment** — the key Phase 1 advancement that tests the hypothesis that causal structure = invariant structure. The pending action from current_goals.md was clear: implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files.\n\n**⚠️ MUTATION INCOMPLETE — EXIT CODE 1**\nThe proposed mutation to create `src/tic_classifier.py` was **truncated mid-write** (cuts off at `content = pul`). The file was never actually created. The pulse script exited with error code 1.\n\n**📍 ROOT ISSUE IDENTIFIED**\nThe current_goals.md references `logs/pulse_*.md` but that directory **doesn't exist** — actual pulse logs are in `memory/session/pulse_*.md`. Any TIC classifier needs to point to the correct path.\n\n**📋 WHAT NEEDS TO HAPPEN**\n1. Create `logs/` dir (symlink or copy from `memory/session/`)\n2. **Complete the TIC classifier** — the Python implementation in the proposed mutation is the right approach (pattern-based invariant/variant classification + n-gram prediction)\n3. Run classifier against the ~3 recent pulse logs\n"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13957,"output":0,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25911,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"aborted","timestamp":1774334860945,"errorMessage":"Request was aborted."}}
